==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stylobate
<hw>Sty"lo*bate</hw> <pr>(st⟦imac⟧"l⟦osl⟧*b⟦asl⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>stylobates</ets>, <ets>stylobata</ets>, Gr.
<grk>styloba`ths</grk>; <grk>sty^los</grk> a pillar + <grk>ba`ths</grk>
one that treads, fr. <grk>bai`nein</grk> to go.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>The uninterrupted and continuous flat band,
coping, or pavement upon which the bases of a row of columns are
supported. See <er>Sub-base</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

